    <head>FRANKENSTEIN.</head>
    
    <ab rend="italic">By the glimmer of the half-extinguished</ab>
    <ab rend="italic">light, I saw the dull yellow eye of the</ab>
    <ab rend="italic">creature open; it breathed hard, and a</ab>
    <ab rend="italic">convulsive motion agitated its limbs,</ab>
    <ab rend="italic">* * * I rushed out of the room.</ab>
    <ab rend="italic">Page 43.</ab>
    <ab rend="italic">London. Published by H Colburn and R Bentley, 1831.</ab>
